Red Tide Current Status Report (27 May 2005)
--------------------------------------------
Map of Red Tide Counts (22 May 2005):
<http://www.floridamarine.org/images/articles/12373/12373_4031.jpg>

Ref. by sender:
<http://research.myfwc.com/images/gallery/20050527_143955_10640.jpg>

Red Tide Current Status Report (27 May 2005)
Present Status: The current red tide bloom continues between lower
Tampa Bay and Sarasota Bay. Low concentrations of _Karenia brevis_,
the Florida red tide organism, were also found as far south as
Venice, indicating a slight southward trend in bloom movement. Fish
kills and respiratory irritation were reported from Longboat Key,
Siesta Key, Casey Key, and Englewood. Red tide effects are possible
along coastal beaches with onshore winds and in bay areas as long as
above-normal concentrations of _K. brevis_ remain.

Bloom Boundary North (alongshore): Manatee County
Bloom Boundary South (alongshore): Sarasota County

